  "prompt": "Any suggested cellphone units to make me active on messanger all the time using only my data?",
  "response": "Certainly! When looking for a cellphone that will keep you active on Messenger using data, you should consider the following criteria: reliable network connectivity, long battery life, and efficient performance. Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. **Apple iPhone 13/14**:\n   - **Pros**: High performance, excellent camera, reliable internet connectivity, iOS ecosystem.\n   - **Cons**: Higher price point.\n\n2. **Samsung Galaxy S22/S23**:\n   - **Pros**: High performance, great camera, reliable internet connectivity, Android ecosystem.\n   - **Cons**: Higher price point.\n\n3. **Google Pixel 7**:\n   - **Pros**: Pure Android experience, excellent camera, reliable connectivity.\n   - **Cons**: Battery life may vary with usage.\n\n4. **OnePlus 10 Pro**:\n   - **Pros**: High performance, good battery life, reliable network connectivity.\n   - **Cons**: Slightly less polished software.\n\n5. **Xiaomi Mi 12/13**:\n   - **Pros**: High performance, good battery life, reasonable price.\n   - **Cons**: MIUI software may not appeal to everyone.\n\n6. **Motorola Moto G Power (2022)**:\n   - **Pros**: Excellent battery life, reliable performance, budget-friendly.\n   - **Cons**: Lower camera quality compared to flagship models.\n\nWhen choosing a cellphone, ensure it supports the latest LTE/5G bands for optimal data connectivity. Additionally, consider setting up your device to minimize battery consumption when using Messenger, such as adjusting background app refresh settings and enabling power-saving modes when necessary.",
